<section class="sec reveal" id="qbd-byline">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="byline">
      <span class="byline__mark" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 64 64" fill="#FCFBF8"><path d="M8 10 H38 V54 H26 V22 H8 Z"/><rect x="42" y="10" width="14" height="12"/></svg></span>
      <div>
        <p class="byline__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline__meta">Reviewed by a QuickBooks Desktop &amp; Enterprise ProAdvisor &middot; independent, no reseller incentive</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="qbd-credentials">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Certified by Intuit &middot; Desktop, Enterprise, Online (L2), Payroll</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials.</h2>
    <div class="r-3" style="margin-bottom:26px;">
      {%- for s in credStats %}
      <div><div class="mono" style="font-size:30px;font-weight:500;color:var(--color-accent);">{{ s.value }}</div><div style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:8px;">{{ s.label }}</div></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <ul class="checklist">
      {%- for c in credentials %}<li>{{ c | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbd-definition" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In plain terms</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">What QuickBooks Desktop is &mdash; and where it&rsquo;s going.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- AI-SUMMARY renders via the t-prose layout slot (sec.aiH); not duplicated here. -#}

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbd-editions" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The four Desktop editions</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Pro, Premier, Mac, Enterprise.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Editions differ on user count, industry-specific features, and inventory depth. Enterprise sits in its own tier &mdash; it&rsquo;s effectively a different product and has its own positioning. For specific pricing, check Intuit directly &mdash; we don&rsquo;t publish their numbers because they change. Not sure which fits? <a href="/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review">Start with a free file review</a> &mdash; no commission, an honest answer.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for e in editions %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ e.tier }}</span><h3>{{ e.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ e.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="qbd-vs">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The editions, head to head</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Pro Plus vs Premier Plus vs Mac Plus vs Enterprise.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:72ch;">An honest comparison of the four Desktop editions &mdash; user counts, industry features, inventory depth, and where each stands in Intuit&rsquo;s wind-down. We hold no reseller incentive in any direction.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">QuickBooks Desktop editions compared — Pro Plus, Premier Plus, Mac Plus, and Enterprise</caption>
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Capability</th><th scope="col">Pro Plus</th><th scope="col">Premier Plus</th><th scope="col">Mac Plus</th><th scope="col">Enterprise</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for r in vsTable %}
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Capability">{{ r.cap | safe }}</th>
          <td data-col="Pro Plus">{% if r.pro == 'yes' %}<span class="mark-yes"></span><span class="sr-only">Yes</span>{% elif r.pro == 'no' %}<span class="mark-no"></span><span class="sr-only">No</span>{% else %}{{ r.pro | safe }}{% endif %}</td>
          <td data-col="Premier Plus">{% if r.premier == 'yes' %}<span class="mark-yes"></span><span class="sr-only">Yes</span>{% elif r.premier == 'no' %}<span class="mark-no"></span><span class="sr-only">No</span>{% else %}{{ r.premier | safe }}{% endif %}</td>
          <td data-col="Mac Plus">{% if r.mac == 'yes' %}<span class="mark-yes"></span><span class="sr-only">Yes</span>{% elif r.mac == 'no' %}<span class="mark-no"></span><span class="sr-only">No</span>{% else %}{{ r.mac | safe }}{% endif %}</td>
          <td class="num us" data-col="Enterprise">{% if r.ent == 'yes' %}<span class="mark-yes"></span><span class="sr-only">Yes</span>{% elif r.ent == 'no' %}<span class="mark-no"></span><span class="sr-only">No</span>{% else %}{{ r.ent | safe }}{% endif %}</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbd-sunset" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What the sunset actually means</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Six things to understand about Intuit&rsquo;s Desktop wind-down.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Most of what you&rsquo;ll read online about &ldquo;Desktop being killed&rdquo; is half-right. Here&rsquo;s the actual picture.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in sunset %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="qbd-stay">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Who genuinely still needs Desktop</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">When staying on Desktop is the right call today.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Not everyone should migrate right now. These are the cases where Desktop is genuinely still the better answer &mdash; for now.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for n in stay %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ n.num }}</span><h3>{{ n.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ n.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbd-go" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Who should plan the move now</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">When migration is the right call.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Counterpart to &ldquo;who should stay&rdquo; &mdash; the situations where moving to QBO sooner rather than later is the genuinely correct decision.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for m in migrate %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ m.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ m.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="qbd-routing">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Your situation</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">Where are you with QuickBooks Desktop?</h2>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for b in routing %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ b.href }}"><h3>{{ b.opener | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ b.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ b.cta | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbd-services" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How we support Desktop businesses</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Through the Desktop years &mdash; and the migration when it&rsquo;s time.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">TechBrot ProAdvisors handle the full Desktop lifecycle &mdash; while you&rsquo;re on it, when problems develop, and when migration becomes the right call.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in services %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3><a href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.name | safe }}</a></h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="qbd-operator">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Who performs the work</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Certified on both sides of the Desktop-to-Online line.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Supporting a Desktop business means being fluent in Desktop today and ready for the migration tomorrow. Every TechBrot ProAdvisor holds active certifications on both Desktop and Online (Level 2) plus Enterprise and Payroll &mdash; so the team that supports your Desktop file today is the same team that handles your migration when the time is right.</p>
      <p>We earn nothing from your QuickBooks subscription &mdash; no Desktop license fees, no QBO referral commissions, no affiliate revenue. The recommendation you get reflects what fits your business, not what pays us. You can <a href="/quickbooks/proadvisor-team/">meet the ProAdvisor team</a> or read our <a href="/trust/">trust &amp; methodology standards</a>. Independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row" style="margin-top:22px;">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbd-related" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Other QuickBooks products</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">Related QuickBooks options.</h2>
    {%- for n in related %}
    <div style="margin-bottom:18px;">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
